Pronotum cordate, widest in front of middle; anterior angles obtuse, posterior rectangular; sides finely margined, coarsely crenulate at lateral lobes; anterior margin shallowly arcuate over median 3/4, without hyaline border; discal reliefs strongly shining, very finely and very sparsely punctulate, without setae. Anterior and posterior ¼ and lateral lobes coarsely deeply punctate. Discal foveae (
Fig. 200
